description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated Pharmacy Technician to lead our Homecare Team. The successful candidate will have good verbal and written communication skills, be a strong team player and able to work using their own initiative, within the limits of the job role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will ideally have a good working knowledge of homecare ranging from commissioning, through to the procurement aspects. You will be responsible for co-ordinating processes for the introduction of homecare services for new medicines, including the development and implementation of local policies, in liaison with the Specialist Pharmacists and homecare providers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be able to enhance or develop your managerial skills being responsible for recruitment of staff to the team, including advertising, short-listing, interviewing and selecting staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will support the maintenance of any held qualifications eg. ACPT, Practice Supervisor and will encourage progression in line with the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Name Rosemary Vambe Job title Pharmacy Purchasing, Homecare and IPP Team Manager Email address rosemary.vambe@gosh.nhs.uk Telephone number 0207 405 9200 Ext 5336&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
